[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/reverse_drury"]
[Student "S"]
{With 11 points in support of \Hs you would generally make a limit raise with this hand. But since partner is in third seat you need to go carefully in case he has opened light. So you bid a Reverse Drury 2\C.

Partner rebids 2\H. What do you say next? 

Partner's 2\H rebid tells you that he opened light. So you pass.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "W"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "W:Q874.A53.KQ3.T82 63.T762.AT8.KQ74 AKJ95.Q94.76.965 T2.KJ8.J9542.AJ3"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "2S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "W"]
pass pass 1S pass 2C pass 2S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "f58f0c9b827448ab9fa94bfa9c972d17074d2982cd2bdf2cb9eb348a661aced6"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/reverse_drury"]
[Student "S"]
{You open in third seat and the bidding continues as shown.  

Partner has a limit raise in \Ss and wonders if you have a full strength opening bid. Since you opened light you just return to \Ss at the minimum level.

Partner passes.}

